# Database structure - generated from running Postgres container (Oct 2025)

This file summarizes tables, columns, primary keys and foreign keys for the `api_recetas_postgres` database (schema: public).

Tables (public):

-- See `tables.txt` for full list

Columns: brief listing (see `columns.txt` for full detail)

-- categoria
   - id_cat (PK) : integer
   - nombre : character varying
   - url_imagen : character varying
   - estado : smallint (default 1)
   - fecha_creacion : timestamp (default now())
   - comentario : character varying
   - id_usr : integer

-- receta
   - id_receta (PK) : integer
   - nombre : character varying
   - url_imagen : character varying
   - ingrediente : text
   - preparacion : character varying
   - estado : smallint (default 1)
   - id_cat : integer (FK -> categoria.id_cat)
   - id_pais : integer (FK -> pais.id_pais)
   - fecha_creacion : date (default now())
   - id_usr : integer (FK -> usuario.id_usr)
   - visitas : integer (default 0)

-- usuario
   - id_usr (PK) : integer
   - nombre, apellido, email, password
   - estado : smallint (default 1)
   - fecha_creacion : timestamp (default now())
   - comentario : character varying
   - id_perfil : integer (FK -> perfil.id_perfil)

Primary keys: see `pks.txt` (excerpt)

Foreign keys: see `fks.txt` (excerpt)

Notes:
- The `carrusel` table has been removed; carrusel content is computed dynamically by the API (`GET /recetas/carrusel`).
- For a full, machine-readable dump of columns and relations, review `columns.txt`, `pks.txt`, `fks.txt` and `ER_diagrama_ascii.txt`.
